WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:01.382
Look!

2
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:09.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-

3
00:00:24.344 --> 00:00:27.643
Now that is not a bear.

4
00:00:34.387 --> 00:00:36.249
It was like hitting a stone wall.

5
00:00:36.289 --> 00:00:37.450
I hit it with all I had.

6
00:00:37.490 --> 00:00:39.386
Ran. Just like you ran from my father.

7
00:00:39.426 --> 00:00:41.388
I'll cut your tongue out. boy.
Stop!

8
00:00:41.428 --> 00:00:42.759
Both of you.

9
00:00:42.896 --> 00:00:45.057
That thing is still out there!

10
00:00:45.198 --> 00:00:46.660
The gods have cursed us all.

11
00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:48.328
We should leave this place while
we can still save our families.

12
00:00:48.368 --> 00:00:49.329
This is our home!

13
00:00:49.369 --> 00:00:51.331
We are not going to let
that thing chase us out!

14
00:00:51.371 --> 00:00:52.699
She's right! We're not leaving.

15
00:00:52.739 --> 00:00:55.402
We're going to hunt this thing
down and kill it like Vikings.

16
00:00:55.442 --> 00:00:57.000
Hunting won't work.

17
00:01:01.481 --> 00:01:03.310
You can't take it on in the open.

18
00:01:03.350 --> 00:01:04.311
It's too powerful.

19
00:01:04.351 --> 00:01:05.712
Well. what else is there?

20
00:01:05.752 --> 00:01:07.185
We trap it.

21
00:01:09.089 --> 00:01:11.057
Even if you do track it down.

22
00:01:11.291 --> 00:01:13.205
How are you going to kill it?

23
00:01:13.326 --> 00:01:15.622
Why are we even listening to him?
He's not one of us.

24
00:01:15.662 --> 00:01:17.114
That's right. I'm not.

25
00:01:17.197 --> 00:01:18.959
But you're wrong about this. Wulfric.

26
00:01:18.999 --> 00:01:21.695
Like you were wrong about and the bear.

27
00:01:21.835 --> 00:01:25.861
And you'll always be wrong until
you stop thinking with this.

28
00:01:28.241 --> 00:01:29.936
This is finished!

29
00:01:30.343 --> 00:01:31.729
You're not one of us.

30
00:01:31.745 --> 00:01:33.645
The decision is ours.

31
00:01:33.880 --> 00:01:37.441
However. I'm still your king.

32
00:01:38.451 --> 00:01:41.685
And my judgment is that
the Outlander is correct.

33
00:01:46.059 --> 00:01:47.720
We build the trap.

34
00:01:55.168 --> 00:01:56.863
So.

35
00:01:58.238 --> 00:01:59.865
where do we start?

36
00:02:00.874 --> 00:02:02.273
Here…

37
00:02:06.479 --> 00:02:09.607
And ending… here.

38
00:02:18.391 --> 00:02:20.120
What are you waiting for?

39
00:02:20.794 --> 00:02:21.954
Dig!

40
00:02:39.879 --> 00:02:42.245
The forge. what does it burn?

41
00:02:43.650 --> 00:02:44.878
Wood.

42
00:02:45.051 --> 00:02:47.451
What about the torches. the lamps?

43
00:02:47.587 --> 00:02:49.054
Whale oil.

44
00:02:49.456 --> 00:02:50.684
I'll need it.

45
00:02:51.257 --> 00:02:51.882
How much?

46
00:02:52.025 --> 00:02:53.322
All of it.

47
00:03:16.850 --> 00:03:18.044
How's it coming?

48
00:03:20.453 --> 00:03:22.182
Is it deep enough for you?

49
00:03:22.422 --> 00:03:23.252
No.

50
00:03:23.390 --> 00:03:24.721
Four more feet.

51
00:03:25.225 --> 00:03:26.677
And when you got that…

52
00:03:26.693 --> 00:03:29.589
I need two rows of postholes
running up both sides.

53
00:03:29.629 --> 00:03:30.687
Post holes?

54
00:03:30.830 --> 00:03:31.194
Yeah.

55
00:03:31.331 --> 00:03:33.561
What do you need post holes for?

56
00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:35.097
Posts.

57
00:03:35.335 --> 00:03:36.427
Posts.

58
00:03:38.638 --> 00:03:39.570
Posts.

59
00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:08.260
Are we done now?

60
00:04:08.401 --> 00:04:09.459
Not yet.

61
00:04:09.602 --> 00:04:12.036
Not yet? What's left?

62
00:04:13.807 --> 00:04:14.899
Shields?

63
00:04:15.041 --> 00:04:16.338
Shields.

64
00:05:14.334 --> 00:05:16.802
When this thing is over…

65
00:05:18.338 --> 00:05:20.252
there's a place here for you.

66
00:05:21.875 --> 00:05:23.172
Should you wish it.

67
00:06:17.564 --> 00:06:18.792
You hungry?

68
00:06:38.218 --> 00:06:39.549
What about you?

69
00:06:41.721 --> 00:06:43.283
I'll eat when you're finished.

70
00:06:43.323 --> 00:06:44.415
No.

71
00:06:44.724 --> 00:06:45.952
You sit.

72
00:06:50.096 --> 00:06:51.358
Thank you.

73
00:07:03.843 --> 00:07:06.285
I saw you talking to my father today.

74
00:07:09.649 --> 00:07:10.911
What did he say?

75
00:07:13.319 --> 00:07:14.684
He asked me to stay.

76
00:07:18.224 --> 00:07:19.346
What did you say?

77
00:07:24.264 --> 00:07:25.253
Freya…

78
00:07:32.839 --> 00:07:35.611
You don't even know
what kind of man I am.

79
00:07:37.076 --> 00:07:38.202
I know enough.

80
00:07:38.578 --> 00:07:39.943
No. you don't.

81
00:07:45.251 --> 00:07:46.650
So. tell me.

82
00:07:53.426 --> 00:07:54.893
Kainan?

83
00:07:58.931 --> 00:08:01.439
My people are no different than yours.

84
00:08:03.569 --> 00:08:04.831
Hungry for land.

85
00:08:06.172 --> 00:08:08.614
So when we found
an island we wanted.

86
00:08:10.310 --> 00:08:11.334
we took it.

87
00:08:22.622 --> 00:08:26.718
It didn't matter that it already
belonged to something else…

88
00:08:29.062 --> 00:08:32.589
Moorwens. Millions of them.

89
00:08:34.600 --> 00:08:35.760
But we wanted it.

90
00:08:37.770 --> 00:08:40.767
After all. we told ourselves
they were nothing.

91
00:08:40.807 --> 00:08:44.334
Just animals. Beasts.

92
00:08:52.051 --> 00:08:55.282
So we killed them all with fire.

93
00:09:14.040 --> 00:09:16.508
Those we missed. we hunted down.

94
00:10:04.090 --> 00:10:06.251
You obeyed your king's orders.

95
00:10:06.592 --> 00:10:07.920
You didn't have a choice.

96
00:10:07.960 --> 00:10:09.689
You always have a choice.

97
00:10:14.801 --> 00:10:18.464
Land that belonged to the Moorwens
now belonged to us.

98
00:10:31.884 --> 00:10:35.844
As part of my pay I was given a place
for my family to live.

99
00:10:36.556 --> 00:10:40.054
And I thought I could forget
what I'd done to get it.

100
00:10:40.092 --> 00:10:42.666
Some things you can't
bury deep enough.

101
00:10:44.130 --> 00:10:46.030
Hey! What are you doing?

102
00:10:46.165 --> 00:10:48.565
That plant. it stung me.
It what?

103
00:10:48.701 --> 00:10:50.498
It stung me.

104
00:10:50.970 --> 00:10:54.204
Let me show you something.
Stay right here. okay?

105
00:11:18.798 --> 00:11:19.958
Kainan.

106
00:11:21.501 --> 00:11:22.763
The guns are up.

107
00:11:22.969 --> 00:11:25.081
And there are none of them left.

108
00:11:25.538 --> 00:11:27.130
You'll be safe.

109
00:11:33.779 --> 00:11:34.505
I love you.

110
00:11:34.580 --> 00:11:36.047
I love you. too.

111
00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:12.102
Three weeks later I got word that
one of the Moorwens had survived.

112
00:12:12.151 --> 00:12:15.587
And it got in our compound
and killed everyone.

113
00:12:19.992 --> 00:12:21.387
It was the will of the gods.

114
00:12:21.427 --> 00:12:22.288
It was their destiny.

115
00:12:22.328 --> 00:12:23.852
There is no destiny.

116
00:12:24.864 --> 00:12:26.661
There is no gods.

117
00:12:30.803 --> 00:12:32.065
It was just me.

118
00:12:34.840 --> 00:12:36.137
And I failed them.

119
00:12:39.745 --> 00:12:41.042
I failed them.

120
00:12:56.562 --> 00:12:58.325
This is a king's sword.

121
00:12:59.398 --> 00:13:01.389
passed down from my ancestors.

122
00:13:02.768 --> 00:13:04.096
My father gave it to me…

123
00:13:04.136 --> 00:13:05.831
and told me that one day

124
00:13:06.038 --> 00:13:08.348
I would know the man to give it to.

125
00:13:08.975 --> 00:13:10.306
A good man.

126
00:13:23.923 --> 00:13:28.015
If you truly believe that you
write the tale of your own life…

127
00:13:29.295 --> 00:13:32.128
then the end is up to you.

128
00:14:05.264 --> 00:14:06.458
More arrows!

129
00:14:19.445 --> 00:14:20.912
The gods be with you.

130
00:14:31.290 --> 00:14:32.985
Boromir. close the doors.

131
00:14:46.238 --> 00:14:47.671
Open the gates!

132
00:15:03.956 --> 00:15:05.540
You sure this will work?

133
00:15:11.197 --> 00:15:12.649
That's what I thought.

134
00:16:18.197 --> 00:16:19.357
Hold this.

135
00:16:41.353 --> 00:16:42.479
Gods above…

136
00:16:57.069 --> 00:16:58.866
Wait for my order!

137
00:17:24.630 --> 00:17:26.610
What's your damn priest doing?

138
00:17:53.692 --> 00:17:56.525
I command thee. Lucifer.

139
00:17:56.662 --> 00:17:58.357
quit this place!

140
00:18:24.356 --> 00:18:25.653
Ready!

141
00:18:42.308 --> 00:18:43.206
Wulfric!

142
00:18:45.044 --> 00:18:46.238
Hold your fire!

143
00:18:48.180 --> 00:18:48.612
Shoot!

144
00:18:48.747 --> 00:18:49.508
Take my hand!

145
00:18:49.548 --> 00:18:50.105
Shoot!

146
00:18:50.249 --> 00:18:52.649
Hold!
Take it now!

147
00:18:56.255 --> 00:18:57.415
Fire!

148
00:19:09.435 --> 00:19:11.460
By the gods!

149
00:19:44.803 --> 00:19:45.770
Freya?

150
00:19:49.575 --> 00:19:50.507
Freya!

151
00:19:51.877 --> 00:19:53.003
Freya!

152
00:20:58.944 --> 00:21:00.343
Moorwen!

153
00:21:29.341 --> 00:21:30.308
Kainan

154
00:21:31.210 --> 00:21:32.530
There's another one!

155
00:22:49.388 --> 00:22:50.548
Kainan!

156
00:22:52.791 --> 00:22:54.045
Everyone's leaving.

157
00:22:59.965 --> 00:23:03.560
Eric. it's not safe here anymore.

158
00:23:04.136 --> 00:23:06.116
Everyone's going to the boats.

159
00:23:06.838 --> 00:23:08.396
You need to go. too.

160
00:23:08.740 --> 00:23:10.984
But. I want to stay here with you.

161
00:23:11.977 --> 00:23:13.638
You'll come back soon.

162
00:23:13.845 --> 00:23:15.210
Everyone will.

163
00:23:15.547 --> 00:23:16.912
You promise?

164
00:23:25.023 --> 00:23:26.217
I promise.

165
00:24:03.629 --> 00:24:05.873
Your boots. do you want them back?

166
00:24:06.498 --> 00:24:09.661
No. They're his now.

167
00:24:12.170 --> 00:24:13.820
What are you going to do?

168
00:24:14.273 --> 00:24:15.501
You're king now.

169
00:24:17.743 --> 00:24:19.108
King of what? This?

170
00:24:20.379 --> 00:24:23.405
This… and them…

171
00:24:25.450 --> 00:24:27.562
Whatever Herot becomes tomorrow…

172
00:24:27.819 --> 00:24:30.525
will be because of
what you do right now.

173
00:24:32.491 --> 00:24:34.141
Let's go kill this thing…

174
00:24:37.162 --> 00:24:38.459
together.

175
00:25:03.322 --> 00:25:04.516
You're daft!

176
00:25:04.656 --> 00:25:06.624
We're not going down there.

177
00:25:06.758 --> 00:25:08.420
That's where it came from.

178
00:25:08.460 --> 00:25:10.110
That's where we're going.

179
00:25:10.262 --> 00:25:12.391
But we don't know how to kill it yet.

180
00:25:12.431 --> 00:25:13.592
We need better weapons.

181
00:25:13.632 --> 00:25:16.658
No. We need better metal.

182
00:25:17.502 --> 00:25:19.416
Boromir. get the forge ready.

183
00:25:19.871 --> 00:25:23.466
Unferth. Olaf. get the torches
and the ropes.

184
00:25:23.942 --> 00:25:25.000
Let's go.

185
00:25:26.078 --> 00:25:27.511
I'm coming with you.

186
00:25:30.849 --> 00:25:32.111
No you're not.

187
00:25:33.285 --> 00:25:36.982
That thing killed my father and
destroyed my home.

188
00:25:37.122 --> 00:25:38.612
I'm coming with you.

189
00:25:46.531 --> 00:25:48.527
This is where your ship went down?

190
00:25:48.567 --> 00:25:50.034
That's right.

191
00:25:56.174 --> 00:25:57.471
In a lake?

192
00:26:01.847 --> 00:26:02.745
Don't ask.

193
00:27:00.172 --> 00:27:01.139
Kainan?

194
00:27:31.970 --> 00:27:33.130
Freya?

195
00:27:34.039 --> 00:27:35.472
Freya?

196
00:27:41.947 --> 00:27:43.039
Where's Freya?

197
00:27:43.748 --> 00:27:46.322
Just get the metal and make the swords!

198
00:27:49.888 --> 00:27:50.946
Damn.

199
00:28:01.433 --> 00:28:03.215
What kind of metal is this?

200
00:28:18.783 --> 00:28:20.250
King's sword again.

201
00:28:50.682 --> 00:28:53.310
You're…
I know. Daft.

202
00:30:22.273 --> 00:30:23.262
Let's go.

203
00:32:53.091 --> 00:32:54.609
Where's it coming from?

204
00:32:58.563 --> 00:32:59.962
It's beneath us.

205
00:33:26.324 --> 00:33:27.382
God.

206
00:33:28.426 --> 00:33:29.723
I slipped.

207
00:33:47.278 --> 00:33:48.466
Let's keep moving.

208
00:33:58.489 --> 00:34:00.139
Ain't nothing down there.

209
00:34:09.200 --> 00:34:11.100
Unferth!
Wulfric!

210
00:34:16.374 --> 00:34:17.760
Can you see anything?

211
00:34:19.244 --> 00:34:20.142
Over here!

212
00:35:47.999 --> 00:35:48.988
Boromir!

213
00:36:14.792 --> 00:36:17.102
We'll drink together again. Kainan.

214
00:36:19.764 --> 00:36:21.026
Herot mead.

215
00:36:23.835 --> 00:36:25.234
Best in the world.

216
00:36:40.551 --> 00:36:42.485
No!

217
00:36:44.789 --> 00:36:46.313
Kainan!

218
00:36:47.225 --> 00:36:49.785
Freya! Freya…!

219
00:36:50.862 --> 00:36:53.228
Kainan!

220
00:36:57.969 --> 00:36:59.129
That way!

221
00:37:00.104 --> 00:37:02.504
Freya!

222
00:37:04.075 --> 00:37:05.133
I'm here.

223
00:37:48.219 --> 00:37:50.847
Freya. Freya.

224
00:38:00.131 --> 00:38:01.223
Freya!

225
00:38:09.173 --> 00:38:10.868
Freya. Squeeze through!

226
00:38:11.976 --> 00:38:12.637
Squeeze through!

227
00:38:12.677 --> 00:38:13.837
Too tight.

228
00:38:14.879 --> 00:38:16.506
Take it!

229
00:38:35.900 --> 00:38:39.495
Freya. calm down. calm down.

230
00:38:45.443 --> 00:38:47.308
By all the gods.

231
00:39:11.936 --> 00:39:12.903
Move!

232
00:39:45.603 --> 00:39:46.729
Over there!

233
00:40:01.285 --> 00:40:02.650
Get her out of here!

234
00:40:09.627 --> 00:40:10.719
Come on!

235
00:40:21.505 --> 00:40:22.597
Swing me!

236
00:40:47.898 --> 00:40:48.922
Wulfric!

237
00:44:44.969 --> 00:44:46.231
Is it dead?

238
00:44:48.939 --> 00:44:49.997
Yes.

239
00:45:00.885 --> 00:45:04.184
I wanted this for so long.

240
00:45:08.826 --> 00:45:11.202
At least I got to wear it for a day.

241
00:45:15.799 --> 00:45:18.505
I hope you wear it for
longer than I did.

242
00:45:21.438 --> 00:45:23.220
We could have been friends.

243
00:45:23.774 --> 00:45:25.435
We are friends.

244
00:46:10.588 --> 00:46:12.453
Eric.

245
00:46:12.723 --> 00:46:13.712
Up here!

246
00:46:14.458 --> 00:46:15.925
Up here!

247
00:46:17.094 --> 00:46:18.061
Up here!

248
00:46:18.195 --> 00:46:19.662
Up here!

249
00:46:35.946 --> 00:46:37.860
You wait here for the others.

250
00:46:38.849 --> 00:46:40.499
I've got something to do.

251
00:46:42.386 --> 00:46:44.498
You're not coming back. are you?

252
00:50:50.067 --> 00:50:52.627
In the year of Four Kings.

253
00:50:53.003 --> 00:50:56.769
Rothgar and Wulfric were laid to rest.

254
00:50:57.207 --> 00:51:00.005
Heroes in the war against the Moorwens.

255
00:51:15.459 --> 00:51:20.226
And Kainan. once a stranger to us…

256
00:51:20.764 --> 00:51:22.391
became king.

257
00:51:24.935 --> 00:51:28.063
He took for himself a wife… and a boy.

258
00:51:28.205 --> 00:51:30.571
who became as his own son.

259
00:52:06.176 --> 00:52:08.406
But only I knew his secret.

260
00:52:10.147 --> 00:52:12.513
That the gods had sent us Kainan.

261
00:52:15.319 --> 00:52:17.959
And when it came time
to return to them…

262
00:52:19.923 --> 00:52:23.518
he chose to stay with us instead.

262
